Only three components were extracted for M2 (Fig. 3b), with time constants of 510 fs, 260 ps, and infinity. The data could be very well fitted without the ultrafast 110 fs component used for M1 (the fitting including this ultrafast component, is shown in Supplementary Note 1 and Supplementary Fig. 3 for comparison). Component-1 corresponded to P* and a minority of B*. Its lifetime, 510 fs, was somewhat longer than the corresponding lifetime for M1. No red shoulder of P GSB corresponding to the PA+PB-\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
