In M3, a similar electronic coherence with a 199 cm−1 frequency was also identified that corresponded to a decrease of the charge separation rate by about two-fold, (190 fs)−1. However, the amplitude of QB was somewhat smaller than that in M1. We speculate that the strength of coherent interaction, i.e., the coupling between P* and PA+PB-\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym}
